\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces (A) The simple comparison: best-of-each, both tuned, both with HIP H every step, same coord system, same step budget — the ``most-faithful'' framing. (B) Sella's variants are different algorithms. We never collapse them under one ``Sella'' row; internal-coords Sella is a different optimizer from Cartesian, etc.\relax }}{1}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
