\newlabel{fig:narrative-irc}{{1}{1}{(A) The simple comparison: best-of-each, both tuned, both with HIP H every step, same coord system, same step budget — the ``most-faithful'' framing. (B) Sella's variants are different algorithms. We never collapse them under one ``Sella'' row; internal-coords Sella is a different optimizer from Cartesian, etc.\relax }{figure.caption.2}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Raw-convergence companion (Sella's library default gate fmax<0.05 left, our canonical fmax<0.01 right). At fmax<0.05 GAD wins by +22pp at 200pm; at fmax<0.01 by +17pp. IRC TOPO is the \emph  {paper headline}, raw conv is supplementary.\relax }}{2}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:narrative-conv}{{2}{2}{Raw-convergence companion (Sella's library default gate fmax<0.05 left, our canonical fmax<0.01 right). At fmax<0.05 GAD wins by +22pp at 200pm; at fmax<0.01 by +17pp. IRC TOPO is the \emph {paper headline}, raw conv is supplementary.\relax }{figure.caption.3}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces IRC TOPO outcomes per (method, noise) — \textbf  {partitioned bars}. Each bar = one method $\times $ one noise level, height = 100\% of $n=287$. Green = both IRC endpoints match labeled R+P by element-aware bond-graph isomorphism (the ``intended'' rate); peach = one endpoint matches; gray = neither. \textbf  {Green segment height is what we report as TOPO-intended.} GAD's green stays at $\sim $45\% even at 200pm; Sella's collapses to $<$25\%, with the loss going partly into ``half'' (one endpoint OK) and ``unintended'' (wrong-saddle failures). Bar edge color encodes method (legend top right).\relax }}{2}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:irc-bars-topo}{{3}{2}{IRC TOPO outcomes per (method, noise) — \textbf {partitioned bars}. Each bar = one method $\times $ one noise level, height = 100\% of $n=287$. Green = both IRC endpoints match labeled R+P by element-aware bond-graph isomorphism (the ``intended'' rate); peach = one endpoint matches; gray = neither. \textbf {Green segment height is what we report as TOPO-intended.} GAD's green stays at $\sim $45\% even at 200pm; Sella's collapses to $<$25\%, with the loss going partly into ``half'' (one endpoint OK) and ``unintended'' (wrong-saddle failures). Bar edge color encodes method (legend top right).\relax }{figure.caption.4}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces TOPO (top) vs RMSD (bottom, $0.3$\,\r A{} threshold) IRC outcomes, same data, two scoring criteria. The strict RMSD criterion has \textbf  {much} smaller green segments because $0.3$\,\r A{} excludes many TOPO-correct endpoints (typical IRC endpoints are 0.35--0.5\,\r A{} from labeled R/P due to conformational breathing). The qualitative shape is the same: GAD wins big at high noise. We treat the TOPO bars as the headline; RMSD bars are for the strict-purist reader.\relax }}{3}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:irc-bars-combined}{{4}{3}{TOPO (top) vs RMSD (bottom, $0.3$\,\AA {} threshold) IRC outcomes, same data, two scoring criteria. The strict RMSD criterion has \textbf {much} smaller green segments because $0.3$\,\AA {} excludes many TOPO-correct endpoints (typical IRC endpoints are 0.35--0.5\,\AA {} from labeled R/P due to conformational breathing). The qualitative shape is the same: GAD wins big at high noise. We treat the TOPO bars as the headline; RMSD bars are for the strict-purist reader.\relax }{figure.caption.5}{}}
